4 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Definitions. As used in [sections 1 through 95] the following definitions
5 apply:
6 (1) "Affiliate of a declarant" means any person who controls, is controlled by, or is under common
7 control with a declarant.
8 (a) A person controls a declarant if the person:
9 (i) is a general partner, officer, director, or employer of the declarant;
10 (ii) directly or indirectly or acting in concert with one or more other persons, or through one or more
11 subsidiaries, owns, controls, holds with power to vote, or holds proxies representing more than 20% of the
12 voting interest in the declarant;
13 (iii) controls in any manner the election of a majority of the directors of the declarant; or
14 (iv) has contributed more than 20% of the capital of the declarant.
15 (b) A person is controlled by a declarant if the declarant:
16 (i) is a general partner, officer, director, or employer of the person;
17 (ii) directly or indirectly or acting in concert with one or more other persons, or through one or more
18 subsidiaries, owns, controls, holds with power to vote, or holds proxies representing more than 20% of the
19 voting interest in the person;
20 (iii) controls in any manner the election of a majority of the directors of the person; or
21 (iv) has contributed more than 20% of the capital of the person.
22 (c) Control does not exist if the powers described in this subsection (1) are held solely as security
23 for an obligation and are not exercised.
24 (2) "Allocated interests" means the following interests allocated to each unit:
25 (a) in a condominium, the undivided interest in the common elements, the common expense
26 liability, and votes in the association;
27 (b) in a cooperative, the common expense liability, the ownership interest, and votes in the
28 association; and
