3 NEW SECTION. Section 6. Eminent domain. (1) If a unit is acquired by eminent domain or part of a
4 unit is acquired by eminent domain leaving the unit owner with a remnant that may not practically or lawfully be
5 used for any purpose permitted by the declaration, the award must include compensation to the unit owner for
6 that unit and its allocated interests, whether or not any common elements are acquired. Upon acquisition,
7 unless the decree otherwise provides, that unit's allocated interests are automatically reallocated to the
8 remaining units in proportion to the respective allocated interests of those units before the taking, and the
9 association shall promptly prepare, execute, and record an amendment to the declaration reflecting the
10 reallocations. Any remnant of a unit remaining after part of a unit is taken under this subsection is thereafter a
11 common element.
12 (2) (a) Except as provided in subsection (1), if part of a unit is acquired by eminent domain, the
13 award must compensate the unit owner for the reduction in value of the unit and its interest in the common
14 elements, whether or not any common elements are acquired.
15 (b) Upon acquisition, unless the decree otherwise provides:
16 (i) that unit's allocated interests are reduced in proportion to the reduction in the size of the unit or
17 on any other basis specified in the declaration; and
18 (ii) the portion of the allocated interests divested from the partially acquired unit are automatically
19 reallocated to that unit and to the remaining units in proportion to the respective allocated interests of those
20 units before the taking, with the partially acquired unit participating in the reallocation on the basis of its reduced
21 allocated interests.
22 (3) If part of the common elements is acquired by eminent domain, the portion of the award
23 attributable to the common elements taken must be paid to the association. Unless the declaration provides
24 otherwise, any portion of the award attributable to the acquisition of a limited common element must be equally
25 divided among the owners of the units to which that limited common element was allocated at the time of
26 acquisition.
27 (4) The court decree must be recorded in every county in which any portion of the common interest
28 community is located.
